nodes.title: AI-Powered Diagnosis System for Rare Diseases
nodes.abstract: This project aims to develop an artificial intelligence-powered diagnostic tool to identify rare diseases based on patient symptoms, genetic data, and medical imaging.

nodes.title: Green Chemistry Solutions for Sustainable Agriculture
nodes.abstract: The project focuses on creating sustainable, eco-friendly chemical processes to produce biofertilizers and pest-control agents.

nodes.title: Quantum Cryptography for Securing IoT Devices
nodes.abstract: This project aims to integrate quantum cryptography techniques into Internet-of-Things (IoT) devices to secure communications against quantum computing attacks.

nodes.title: Harnessing CRISPR for Cancer Immunotherapy
nodes.abstract: The objective of this research is to explore the use of CRISPR-Cas9 technology to engineer immune cells capable of targeting and destroying cancer cells.

nodes.title: Digital Twins for Predictive Maintenance in Smart Factories
nodes.abstract: This proposal seeks to develop digital twin technology to model and predict the behavior of industrial machinery in smart factories.

nodes.title: Sustainable Bioplastics from Algal Biomass
nodes.abstract: This initiative proposes developing biodegradable plastics derived from algal biomass as a sustainable alternative to traditional petroleum-based plastics.

nodes.title: Neural Interfaces for Assistive Robotics
nodes.abstract: The project focuses on developing advanced neural interfaces to control assistive robotic devices for individuals with disabilities.

nodes.title: Smart Grids for Renewable Energy Optimization
nodes.abstract: This project proposes the development of intelligent grid systems to optimize the integration and distribution of renewable energy sources like solar and wind.

nodes.title: Next-Generation Vaccine Platforms Using mRNA
nodes.abstract: This proposal aims to design a scalable platform for rapid mRNA vaccine development to combat emerging infectious diseases.

nodes.title: Oceanic Carbon Capture Using Engineered Microalgae
nodes.abstract: The project explores the potential of genetically engineered microalgae to capture atmospheric carbon dioxide and convert it into bioenergy.
